channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Barnaby’s bold prediction about Porter
item.description: Just a day after he sensationally resigned from the frontbench over concerns about a blind trust, supporters of embattled MP Christian Porter are already lining up to pave the way for his return.

item.title: In-person Emmys open with musical number
item.description: Comedian Cedric the Entertainer opened the 73rd Emmy Awards, the small-screen equivalent of the Oscars, in Los Angeles on Sunday with a group musical number.

item.title: Fears after Covid case at airport for ‘hours’
item.description: Queensland has recorded zero new local cases of Covid-19 but the state is on high alert after an positive case was in Brisbane airport for four hours while infected.

item.title: ‘Highly volatile’: Shocking protest video
item.description: Shocking video has emerged of police appearing to push over an older woman during the violent anti-lockdown protests in Melbourne over the weekend.

item.title: Body found matching description of US missing woman Petito: FBI
item.description: US law enforcement said Sunday a body found in a US national forest in Wyoming, where a search was underway for Gabrielle "Gabby" Petito, matches the description of the missing woman, whose disappearance has gripped the country.

item.title: In-person Emmys return as Netflix eyes TV’s top prize with ‘The Crown’
item.description: Television's top stars gathered on the red carpet for the first time in two years at Sunday's Emmys, where Netflix is tipped to finally win the small screen's biggest prize for "The Crown."

item.title: Name change for tourist hot spot
item.description: Fraser Island has long been known as paradise, and now it’s official.

item.title: Mystery after woman’s body found in cabin
item.description: Police are continuing their investigations into the death of a 34-year-old woman whose body was found in a cabin in a forest on the NSW mid north coast.

item.title: Volcano erupts on Spain’s Canary Islands
item.description: The Cumbre Vieja volcano erupted on Spain's Canary Islands Sunday, spewing out lava, ash and a huge column of smoke after days of increased seismic activity and forcing the evacuation of around 5,000 local people, authorities said.

item.title: Wild scenes as shirtless man arrested
item.description: An angry, shirtless man has been pictured during a wild arrest in Melbourne’s CBD.
